# Equoria CODEOWNERS
#
# Equoria-8vys (B5): lock the doctrine and gate-control surface behind
# human code-owner review. Files in this list require an approved review
# from a code owner before merge — but ONLY when combined with a branch
# protection rule that has "Require review from Code Owners" enabled on
# the protected branch (master). Without that branch-protection setting
# this file is advisory; with it, the lock is binding.
#
# Why this exists: under deadline pressure (or under an autonomous agent's
# completion drive) it is cheaper to weaken the rule than to fix the
# violation. Editing CLAUDE.md to add an exception, narrowing a doctrine-
# check regex, removing a CI gate's `needs:` reference, or adding
# `continue-on-error: true` to a security step are all single-line edits
# that look innocuous in isolation but dissolve enforcement. A CODEOWNERS
# gate makes every such edit surface in a PR review where a human can ask
# "is this a real exception, or are we cutting a corner to make a build
# go green?" The same agent that proposes the weakening is not the
# approver of it.
#
# Self-lock: this file is in its own coverage list (last entry below). An
# attempt to remove the lock by editing CODEOWNERS itself will require
# the same code-owner approval, closing the obvious bypass loophole.
#
# Syntax notes:
#   - Each line: `<pattern> <owner1> [<owner2> ...]`
#   - Patterns follow .gitignore rules; later matches override earlier.
#   - `/path/` matches a directory and everything under it.
#   - `*` and `**` glob; `*.yml` matches one segment, `**/*.yml` recursive.
# Reference: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-customization/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# ── Project-level instructions consumed by every agent session ──────────
/CLAUDE.md @machsheltie

# ── Discipline rules auto-loaded by CLAUDE.md ───────────────────────────
# Includes EDGE_CASE_FIX_DISCIPLINE.md, OPTIMAL_FIX_DISCIPLINE.md,
# COMPLETION_VERIFICATION_POLICY.md, ES_MODULES_REQUIREMENTS.md, etc.
/.claude/rules/ @machsheltie

# ── Machine-checked doctrine scripts wired into CI gates ────────────────
/scripts/doctrine-checks/ @machsheltie

# ── CI workflow definitions ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# All gate logic — security-gate, coverage-gate, beta-readiness-gate,
# deployment-gate — lives inside ci-cd.yml and test.yml as named jobs.
# The original B5 spec called out `*-gate*.yml` but no workflow file in
# this repo uses that naming convention; locking the whole directory is
# both broader and more accurate to intent.
/.github/workflows/ @machsheltie

# ── Self-lock so this file cannot be silently edited ────────────────────
/.github/CODEOWNERS @machsheltie
